'''Thomas "Tommy" Rigg''' (born [[Bedlington]], 20 February 1920, died [[Northumberland]], May 1995)<ref>{{cite book |   first=Roger|last= Triggs |   title=The Men Who Made Gillingham Football Club|   publisher=Tempus Publishing Ltd |   year=2001|   id=ISBN 0-7524-2243-X|pages=287}}</ref> was an [[England|English]] professional [[association football]]er, who played as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]. His clubs included [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]<ref>[http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/watford/watford.htm Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Database]</ref> and [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]], where he made nearly 200 [[Football League]] appearances.<ref>[http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/gillingham/gillingham.htm Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Database]</ref> He was related to [[Jimmy Kelly (footballer born 1931)|Jimmy Kelly]], who also played for Watford.<ref>{{citebook|title=The Watford Football Club Illustrated Who's Who|author=Jones, Trefor|date=1996|isbn= 0-9527458-0-1|page=198}}</ref>

